messages.content: Wanderer was cautiously waiting for Caeli outside of a portal. If she looked inside, she could see Rome.

“Cae!” She said happily, arms widening.
*he runs up to Wanderer and hugs her with a smile on his face* I'm back!
She hugged him back, giggling. “W-Welcome back!”
*he jumps into the air and flies for a bit before landing* Man, it's good being able to fly again!
“Yeah! You must feel sky high to have it again!” She said, jumping up and down.
Yep! I sure am! Oh! I found something that I'd think you'd like!
“Oh? What?” She asked.
Ya know how earlier ya asked for me to get ya a notebook?
Her eyes widened. “Y-You got it?”
Yup! I sure did! This one is super special too!
“I-It is?” She asked.
Yeah, there's this really cool Stand in it! They call themselves Time Warp.
Her eyes widened. “H-He’s in there?!”
Yeah! Why? Is he one of ya Earth friend?
“Y-Yes, he is!”
Oh cool! Don't blame ya, he's a cool dude!
“H-He really is!” She smiled.
“O-Oh, can I see the book?”
OH! Of course ya can! Here ya go! *he hands the notebook to Wanderer*
She smiled, excitedly opening it up.
“T-Time Warp! Welcome to the Void!”
T:Wanderer! It's nice to see you again! It's been a while since I've seen you like that!
“I-I know! But now there’s a you who can stay here with me!”
Nice! *he turns towards Caeli* Oh! Who's that? Are they one of your Void friends?
“Y-Yeah! This is Caeli, although you know him better as...” she allows Caeli to introduce himself.
C: Narancia! *he flies into the sky and lands*
She nodded, smiling. “We all have our own special powers, kind of like our stands are built into our bodies!”

T: Wow, that's so cool!
“Right?! Oh, a-and I can absorb things!

She smiled, clearly happy to have him with her.

"*JOLYNE!*" Polaris screams, his body launching into the portal zone with an unceremonious bang. His body skids on the ground, Polaris putting his arms over his head to soften the blow to it as he falls head first to the ground.

Laying there, Polaris removes their arms and rolls over onto their back, panting. They sit up, still panting, and roll up their pant sleeve... cracks appear all along the lower part of their leg, the insides of the cracks glowing with stars and galaxies inside of them. Another scar. Luckily it'll be easy to cover— just have to stop wearing shorts.

Sighing, Polaris gets up, proceeding to once again fall over. Their leg was burning— and although he shouldn't, he remembers why. Kira.... that mother fucker. Once he meets the Reaper performing as him, they're gonna kick his ass.
He gets up, one more time, and tries putting pressure on his good leg— er, more like the leg that isn't burning *as bad.*

Pulling out his tesseract, he reports short and simple, as usual.
**Mission failed. Joseph Joestar alive, Hayato Kawajiri alive, Kishibe Rohan deceased, Josuke Higashikata unknown, Okuyasu Nijimura unknown, Koichi Hirose alive, Noriaki Kakyoin deceased, Jolyne Cujoh alive, Jotaro Kujo deceased, obviously. Kira Yoshikage, killer of Rohan Kishibe, Noriaki Kakyoin, potentially Josuke Higashikata and Okuyasu Nijimura, and Jotaro Kujo, alive.**

Wanderer was packing for her extended trip to earth, her tail stiff as steel.
There was the sound of rustling and huffing behind wanderer. “W-Why. isn’t it. *fitting??*” a voice irritatedly speaks between huffs.
“H-Huh?” She tensed up for a moment, before turning around, and seeing...another young mun!

What a truly wondrous sight, Iuvenis, the fool, was trying to stuff an **entire telescope**, (while it was still attached to its stand mind you) in an already packed bag. Looking up to the source of the noise though, he notices the spectator to their predicament, “O-Oh!”
“D-Do you want me to help?” She asked, approaching the boy. While she did think it was a little weird that he was trying to stuff a telescope in his bag, it must have meant something to him, right?
As she approaches him, He tenses up as if the girl were to attack him, but at the suggestion of help, the boy nods quickly, though shyly looks away afterwords, “Mhm.”
“D-Dont worry, I’m not gonna hurt you...I don’t wanna hurt anyone.” She said, pulling out her own packed, but less packed than his, bags out.
“O-O-Ok” he stutters out, then quietly kneeling next to his bags, seeing Wanderer’s own, Iuvenis looks back at her, “l-leaving to-too?”
She nodded. “M-My parents don’t want me to be apart of whatever’s gonna happen...”
“P-Parents?”
“Y-Yeah, i actually live with a mom and dad!” She said, before looking saddened. “I-I do guess it’s kinda weird...”
“N-No! It’s no-not weird!” He frantically waves, then pauses, “w-w-what’s it like w-with pa-parents?”
“I-It’s Nice! We all live together, w-we run a bakery together, a-and we read stories and play songs and...” she sighs wistfully.
“Wo-Wow....that sounds,....*w-wonderful*...” his head drops down sadly, seemingly looking at a  photograph half buried beneath the other objects.
Her ears droop a bit, before her attention is drawn to the photo. “H-Hmm...?” She made a curious noise.
“H-Huh?” Looking back up to Wanderer, his ears tilt in confusion.
“Th-That picture...” she gestured at it.
“T-This..?” Grabbing it from the cluster of objects, he shows it to her, “it’s a picture of me and my brother...or..I think he’s my brother...it’s been a while..” he mumbles the last bit.
She looked it over. “M-Maybe he can find him when we get to earth? ...Do you *w-want* to see him?”
